The article discusses the actions taken by the Administration to address the impacts of extreme weather worsened by climate change. The President has been briefed on Tropical Storm Harold and FEMA has pre-deployed personnel to Texas to assist with response and recovery efforts. FEMA is also prepared to provide additional resources if needed. The President has also been briefed on Tropical Storm Franklin, and FEMA has pre-deployed personnel and resources to Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. People in the storm's path are urged to follow state and local guidance.